{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21ed-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7110"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7110"},"text":"§ 7110.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Regular Army: strength in grade; general officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21ee-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7110/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Subject to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s526"},"text":"section 526 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the authorized strength of the Regular Army in general officers on the active-duty list is 75/10,000 of the authorized strength of the Regular Army in commissioned officers on the active-duty list."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21ef-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7110/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The authorized strength of each of the following branches—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21f0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7110/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" each corps of the Army Medical Department; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21f1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7110/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Chaplains;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"in general officers on the active-duty list of the Regular Army is 5/1,000 of the authorized strength of the branch concerned in commissioned officers on the active-duty list of the Regular Army. Not more than one-half of the authorized strength in general officers in such a branch may be in a regular grade above brigadier general.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21f2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7110/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" When the application of the percentages and ratios specified in this section results in a fraction, a fraction of one-half or more is counted as one, and a fraction of less than one-half is disregarded.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaadc21f3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/174"},"text":"70A Stat. 174","children":[],"tail":", § 3210; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861/s1/66"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861, § 1(66)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1463"},"text":"72 Stat. 1463","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/603/s1/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–603, § 1(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/846"},"text":"80 Stat. 846","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/329"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–329","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-06-04"},"text":"June 4, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"